Alan Arkin and John Goodman are very charming in the role of Hollywood co-workers, but their characters deserve more space and they're far from the only ones in the film.
Affleck's film kind of loses its dramatic pull, it is a film that can be watched with a slight interest, appreciate the realization and retro style of the evoking thrillery of the 1970s.
